<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Tax expert Robert Wood uses the analogy of lost a Bitcoin <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/robertwood/2014/03/23/finding-lost-bitcoin-could-mean-irs-finds-you/">to remind you</a> that under United States tax law, if you find something, it is generally considered income unless you can show it was yours all along.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Technology</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Hewlett-Packard will <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/dallas/news/2014/03/20/hp-to-unveil-plans-for-3-d-printing-in-june.html">unveil plans for</a> 3-D printing in June.</p>
